-- Kuwait To Seek Bids for Boosting Electricity Output by 1,900 Megawatts
-- B y   D a h l i a   K h o l a i f
-- 2010-10-26T08:43:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-26/kuwait-to-seek-bids-for-boosting-electricity-output-by-1-900-megawatts.html
Kuwait plans to issue tenders to
increase its production capacity for electricity by 1,900
megawatts and water by 132 million gallons, Prime Minister
 Sheikh Nasser al-Mohammed Al Sabah  told the nation’s parliament.  He gave no details in his comments today about plans for new
power stations or water treatment plants, or the possible
expansion of existing facilities. Kuwait’s current capacity for
generating electricity is 12,000 megawatts a day, and its
capacity for water production is 400 million gallons.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Dahlia Kholaif  in Kuwait at 
 dkholaif@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
